The paper discusses the design and implementation of an open source project aimed at bringing the power of AI to the command line interface. This falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves the use of AI techniques to enhance the command line interface. Additionally, the paper discusses the end user interaction patterns enabled by this design, which falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing techniques to enable the command line interface, which falls under the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to improve the system, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the platform and its impact on software engineering practices, which falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE).
